Cell["\<\
File info Description:

Defines the dataset registry for the entire analysis. Establishes the working \
directory, and stores a structured lookup table called datainfo that maps \
each dataset shorthand (e.g., HeLa_v1, Jurkat) to its CSV filename and two \
sets of pixel coordinate ranges: one for the representative GC view used in \
figures, and one for the broader nucleoplasmic area view.

Functions:
\[Bullet] datainfo \[LongDash] a nested Mathematica list acting as the \
dataset registry: each entry holds {shorthand name, CSV filename, \
{representative view xy ranges}, {full nucleoplasmic view xy ranges}}

\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.987051804411488*^9, 
  3.987051825950049*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3a8655bd-216b-4a53-89f3-\
4ccbefc54eca"],

Cell["\<\
structure:
1) File short hand
2) saved csv (see previous section). note that the file name contains (a) \
name of data set, (b) x and y followed by beg and end used for code and the z \
slice.
3) View used for representative GC
4) Total view including Nucleoplasmic area adjacent\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9823813990965443`*^9, 
  3.982381538702806*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"8662267b-9500-45ec-9752-\
