Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["generic code", "Subtitle",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.982381269097794*^9, 3.9823812694353237`*^9}, {
  3.982381348693367*^9, 
  3.9823813495316277`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"c0b8db7f-a46a-48b1-89a0-\
30b386397c60"],

Cell["\<\
Generic code description:

Reusable Mathematica utility functions used across all subsequent sections. \
Defines display helpers, the custom fire colormap, the radial shell \
convolution kernel for RDF binning, all image import and rendering functions, \
and the full pipeline for computing, fitting, and extracting quantitative \
features from the RDF curves.

Display utilities:
\[Bullet] showQ[bool, leg] \[LongDash] conditionally returns a plot legend \
element or an empty string; used to toggle legends on and off in figures \
without restructuring the plotting code
\[Bullet] firemode / firemodeimage \[LongDash] defines a 32-stop custom fire \
colormap as an RGB lookup table, and a paired function that applies it to a \
grayscale Image using ImageApply and Clip to map intensity to color

Radial shell kernel:
\[Bullet] conv \[LongDash] precomputes a lookup table grouping all integer \
pixel offsets (i, j) within a 20-pixel radius into radial shells sorted by \
distance; each shell entry contains its distance and a sparse binary kernel \
used later by ImageConvolve during RDF calculation

Data import and image rendering:
\[Bullet] emImportData[name, file, xys] \[LongDash] imports a CSV file \
relative to the notebook directory into emData[name], stores x and y \
coordinate ranges in emXRange and emYRange, and returns {name, xys, \
dimensions}; overloaded form without xys omits the range storage
\[Bullet] getImg[name, xs, ys] \[LongDash] extracts a pixel subregion from \
emData[name] defined by xs and ys ranges, subtracts the blurred local minimum \
for background normalization, and returns a Mathematica Image; no-argument \
form uses the stored default ranges
\[Bullet] fireImg[name, xs, ys] \[LongDash] same extraction and normalization \
as getImg but applies the fire colormap to produce a false-color intensity \
image; no-argument form uses the stored default ranges

Granule center detection:
\[Bullet] calcCenters[name, xs, ys] \[LongDash] detects the center of each \
condensate/granule in the cropped image through a pipeline: (1) \
background-subtract and normalize the subregion, (2) Binarize at the \
0.5-weighted midpoint between the 0.5th and 99.5th intensity percentiles \
after blurring, (3) Dilation with a radius-2 disk to merge nearby objects, \
(4) DistanceTransform to compute each pixel\[CloseCurlyQuote]s distance to \
the nearest background, (5) MaxDetect on the blurred distance transform to \
locate the center of each object; returns a binary Image marking center pixels

RDF computation and fitting:
\[Bullet] figureRDF[name, xs, ys, options] \[LongDash] master \
figure-generating function: calls getImg and calcCenters, computes the RDF \
via ImageConvolve with the conv kernels, normalizes by mean intensity and \
mean neighbor count, fits a spline with confidence bands, and assembles a \
formatted plot; options control y-axis range, major/minor tick spacing, and \
padding
\[Bullet] getSpline[name] \[LongDash] computes the raw RDF data for a dataset \
by convolving the center image with each radial shell kernel from conv, \
normalizing the resulting intensity profile, then fits a Bernstein-basis \
spline (29 knots, 189 points) with 95% confidence bands using LinearModelFit; \
result is memorized so it is computed only once per dataset

RDF feature extraction:
\[Bullet] smoothsearch[func, start] \[LongDash] a custom adaptive binary \
search that walks along the RDF spline to locate three landmarks: (1) the \
first distance where g(r) drops back to 1 (first equilibrium crossing), (2) \
the first local minimum of g(r) after that crossing, and (3) the second \
crossing back through g(r) = 1; returns {eqCrossingOne, firstMin, \
eqCrossingTwo} with precision 0.01 nm; emits a warning if no global minimum \
is confirmed
\[Bullet] getLocation[name] \[LongDash] applies smoothsearch to each of the \
three spline bands (lower, central, upper) from getSpline, then uses Around \
to express each landmark distance as a value \[PlusMinus] half-width \
uncertainty derived from the confidence band spread; returns the three \
landmark positions with their uncertainties for reporting in figures and \
tables\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9870518776071243`*^9, 3.9870518805808277`*^9}, {
  3.987052078204872*^9, 
  3.98705210740162*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"09e158f2-2ae1-4326-80f9-\
4ab8d5e116c5"],

