Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Load all", "Subtitle",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9826590010571117`*^9, 
  3.982659001956348*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"27c3f1fd-d9e8-414a-b42e-\
780af63fb481"],

Cell["\<\
Load all description:

Applies emImportData to every entry in the datainfo registry using Map (/@), \
loading all dataset CSV files into memory as named arrays with their \
associated coordinate ranges. This is the single data-ingestion step that \
makes all datasets available for subsequent visualization and analysis.

Functions:
\[Bullet] emImportData[...]  /@ datainfo \[LongDash] maps the import function \
over every row of the datainfo registry, populating emData[], emXRange[], and \
emYRange[] for all datasets in one call\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.987051945924478*^9, 
  3.9870519504586563`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"e01a9eb7-5098-47ba-80d0-\
537a20679a88"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"emImportData", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"#", "[", 
      RowBox[{"[", "1", "]"}], "]"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"#", "[", 
      RowBox[{"[", "2", "]"}], "]"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"#", "[", 
      RowBox[{"[", "3", "]"}], "]"}]}], "]"}], "&"}], "/@", 
  "datainfo"}]], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9854004893984203`*^9, 3.985400490713244*^9}},
 CellLabel->"In[38]:=",ExpressionUUID->"8ff1f618-e84b-4f0e-9964-499bf55b9590"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Zoom in: (Figure S5A-D, with additional grayscale shown)", "Subtitle",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.982493353468564*^9, 3.982493355060721*^9}, {
  3.985398399645574*^9, 3.98539841012879*^9}, {3.9853985465175858`*^9, 
  3.9853985605897017`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"8e60a284-a8ad-42e3-92b1-\
5d9f5bf7a9e7"],

Cell["\<\
Zoom in: (Figure S5A-D, with additional grayscale shown) description:

Generates the zoomed EM image panels for supplementary figures S5A\[Dash]D. \
Rather than calling getImg or fireImg, this section directly applies a global \
contrast normalization to specific pixel crops of the raw data, renders both \
grayscale and fire-colormap versions, exports them as PDFs, and computes the \
physical scale of each image in microns from its pixel dimensions. Multiple \
crops are shown: a large whole-cell overview and tighter zoomed-in subregions \
at different coordinate ranges.

Contrast normalization:
\[Bullet] MinMax[Blur[Image[emData[name][[rows, cols]]], 2]] \[LongDash] \
computes the global min and max of a blurred subregion to establish a \
contrast range; stored as minmax and reused across panels to keep intensity \
scales consistent
\[Bullet] (Blur[img, 2] - minmax[[1]]) / (minmax[[2]] - minmax[[1]]) \
\[LongDash] linearly rescales pixel intensities into [0, 1] using the \
precomputed global range; produces the normalized grayscale image used for \
both display and colormap application

Rendering and export:
\[Bullet] firemodeimage[%] \[LongDash] applies the fire colormap to the \
normalized image to produce the false-color panel shown in figures
\[Bullet] Export[NotebookDirectory[] <> \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]filename.pdf\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote], %] \[LongDash] saves each rendered image as a PDF; \
multiple exports for the whole-cell view and each zoomed subregion

Physical scale calculation:
\[Bullet] ImageDimensions[%%] \[LongDash] retrieves the pixel width and \
height of the exported image
\[Bullet] 4. * ImageDimensions[%%] \[LongDash] converts pixel dimensions to \
nanometers using the 4 nm/pixel FIB-SEM voxel size
\[Bullet] % / 1000 \[LongDash] converts nanometers to microns for reporting \
in figure legends\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.987051967169985*^9, 3.987051978272805*^9}, {
  3.987052221532672*^9, 
  3.9870522258145847`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"fdea445d-d8a3-4688-a077-\
a089b0f9cdd8"],

