Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["RDFs and analysis: (Figure S5E-H)", "Subtitle",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.982381357425951*^9, 3.982381359390511*^9}, {
  3.985398497583851*^9, 3.9853985093881283`*^9}, {3.985398567370565*^9, 
  3.9853985872036963`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"daabeb6b-aeb6-44cb-86be-\
205698d7248f"],

Cell["\<\
RDFs and analysis: (Figure S5E-H) description:

Computes, visualizes, and quantitatively summarizes the Radial Distribution \
Functions for all six datasets (four HeLa views, one full HeLa field, one \
Jurkat). The section has three distinct stages: generating the multi-panel \
RDF figure, extracting landmark positions from each RDF curve, and computing \
and plotting mean granule separation statistics across datasets.

Multi-panel RDF figure (Figure S5E):
\[Bullet] figureRDF[name, \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]yRange\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] -> {0.8, 2.}, \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]yMajor\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] -> 0.2, \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]yMinor\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] -> 0.05] \[LongDash] called on each of the six \
datasets with a common y-axis range; produces an individual formatted RDF \
plot per dataset with fitted spline and confidence bands; prints the y-range \
of each spline during evaluation as a diagnostic
\[Bullet] Grid[Partition[..., 2]] \[LongDash] arranges the six individual RDF \
plots into a 3-row, 2-column grid for the composite figure
\[Bullet] Export[NotebookDirectory[] <> \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]AllRDFs.pdf\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote], %] \[LongDash] saves the complete grid as a PDF

RDF landmark extraction (Figure S5F):
\[Bullet] getLocation[name] \[LongDash] called individually on each of the \
six datasets; returns three landmark positions for each (first equilibrium \
crossing, first minimum, second equilibrium crossing) expressed as Around \
values with uncertainty; output is the per-dataset distance measurements \
reported in the figure

Mean granule separation summary (Figure S5G-H):
\[Bullet] Mean /@ Transpose[{#[[1]], #[[2]] - #[[1]], #[[3]] - #[[1]]} & /@ \
{getLocation[...], ...}] \[LongDash] collects all six getLocation results, \
restructures to express minimum and second crossing relative to the first \
crossing, then averages across datasets to produce mean \[PlusMinus] \
uncertainty for each landmark; used as summary statistics for the bar/error \
figure
\[Bullet] showQ[bool, Round[i]] \[LongDash] used when building the summary \
figure\[CloseCurlyQuote]s tick labels to conditionally display axis tick \
values at specified intervals
\[Bullet] Export[NotebookDirectory[] <> \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]MeanGranuleSeparation.pdf\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote], %] \
\[LongDash] saves the completed summary figure as a PDF\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.98705199128158*^9, 3.9870519972162046`*^9}, {
  3.987052243221819*^9, 
  3.9870522488910723`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"bbf1aad2-32d3-447c-9e0f-\
61701c89417f"],

